entries.meaning: Having a tab (protruding strip of material).
examples: Letter up a tabbed folder for each different catalog you intend to issue. As you collect matter for this catalog, put it in the one place — the folder devoted to that catalog.

entries.meaning: (computing, graphical user interface) Having tabs (the user interface element).
examples: A tabbed browser can display a different webpage on each tab.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of tab
